      'يعالج PicShift الصور داخل المتصفح على جهازك. لا نرفع صورك إلى خوادمنا للتحويل أو لأي معالجة أخرى، ولا نحتفظ بنسخ من ملفاتك الأصلية أو الناتجة على أنظمة PicShift.',
    filesHeading: 'ماذا يحدث لملفاتك',
    filesItems: [
      'عند اختيار ملف، يحمّله المتصفح إلى الذاكرة المحلية وينفّذ التحويل أو الضغط أو خطوات مماثلة بالكامل على جهازك.',
      'لا يرفع PicShift صورك إلى خوادمنا لمعالجتها.',
      'لا تحتاج إلى التسجيل أو تسجيل الدخول لاستخدام الأدوات.',
    ],
    staysHeading: 'صورك وخوادمنا',
    staysItems: [
      'لا نرفع صورك الأصلية إلى خوادم PicShift.',
      'لا نخزّن صورك بعد المعالجة على خوادم PicShift.',
      'تُنشأ التنزيلات محليًا في متصفحك؛ لا نحتفظ بملفات الصور لدينا.',
    ],
    analyticsHeading: 'زيارات الموقع والتحليلات والإعدادات المحلية',
    analyticsItems: [
      'كأي موقع عام، يسجّل PicShift بيانات زيارة واستخدام اعتيادية (مثل عنوان الصفحة وإشارات عامة للجهاز أو المنطقة). لا تتضمن هذه البيانات ملفات صورك.',
      'نستخدم Cloudflare (الاستضافة وشبكة CDN وCloudflare Web Analytics) وUmami لتحليلات ويب تراعي الخصوصية. تعالج طلبات الويب وإشارات الاستخدام النموذجية، لا محتوى صورك.',
      'مع الإعدادات الحالية، يحتفظ Umami وCloudflare Web Analytics ببيانات التحليلات ستة أشهر لكل منهما. تُخزَّن تفضيلات الواجهة مثل المظهر واللغة والجودة الافتراضية في localStorage للمتصفح.',
    ],
    trustHeading: 'نموذج الأمان والثقة',
    trustText:
      'يبني PicShift على تقليل البيانات: تُعالج الصور على جهازك ولا نطلب إنشاء حساب لاستخدام الخدمة. للنص القانوني الكامل والتحديثات راجع صفحة سياسة الخصوصية.',
  },
  it: {
    intro:
      'PicShift elabora le immagini nel browser sul tuo dispositivo. Non carichiamo le tue immagini sui nostri server per la conversione o altre elaborazioni e non conserviamo copie dei file sorgente o di output sui sistemi PicShift.',
    filesHeading: 'Cosa succede ai tuoi file',
    filesItems: [
      'Quando scegli un file, il browser lo carica in memoria locale ed esegue conversione, compressione o passaggi simili interamente sul tuo dispositivo.',
      'PicShift non carica le tue immagini sui nostri server per elaborarle.',
      'Non serve registrarsi o accedere per usare gli strumenti.',
    ],
    staysHeading: 'Le tue immagini e i nostri server',
    staysItems: [
      'Non carichiamo le immagini originali sui server PicShift.',
      'Non archiviamo le immagini elaborate sui server PicShift.',
      'I download sono generati in locale nel browser; non conserviamo file immagine dalla nostra parte.',
    ],
    analyticsHeading: 'Traffico del sito, analytics e impostazioni locali',
    analyticsItems: [
      'Come qualsiasi sito pubblico, PicShift registra dati abituali di visite e uso (ad esempio URL di pagina e segnali generici di dispositivo o regione). Questi dati non includono i tuoi file immagine.',
      'Usiamo Cloudflare (hosting, CDN, Cloudflare Web Analytics) e Umami per analytics web orientata alla privacy. Elaborano richieste web e segnali d’uso tipici, non il contenuto delle tue immagini.',
      'Con la configurazione attuale, Umami e Cloudflare Web Analytics conservano i dati di analytics per sei mesi. Le preferenze di interfaccia (tema, lingua, qualità predefinita) sono nel localStorage del browser.',
    ],
    trustHeading: 'Modello di sicurezza e fiducia',
    trustText:
      'PicShift si basa sulla minimizzazione dei dati: le immagini sono elaborate sul dispositivo e non chiediamo un account per il servizio. Per il testo legale completo e gli aggiornamenti, vedi la pagina Informativa sulla privacy.',
  },
}[lang] ?? {
  intro:
    'PicShift processes images in your browser on your device. Your images are not uploaded to our servers for conversion or other processing, and we do not keep copies of your source or output images on PicShift systems.',
  filesHeading: 'What happens to your files',
  filesItems: [
    'When you choose a file, your browser loads it into local memory and runs conversion, compression, or similar steps entirely on your device.',
    'PicShift does not upload your images to our servers for processing.',
    'You do not need to register or sign in to use the tools.',
  ],
  staysHeading: 'Images and our servers',
  staysItems: [
    'We do not upload your original images to PicShift servers.',
    'We do not store your processed images on PicShift servers.',
    'Downloads are created locally in your browser; we do not retain image files on our side.',
  ],
  analyticsHeading: 'Site traffic, analytics, and local settings',
  analyticsItems: [
    'Like any public website, PicShift records ordinary visit and usage data (for example page URLs and coarse device or region signals). That traffic data does not include your image files.',
    'We use Cloudflare (hosting, CDN, Cloudflare Web Analytics) and Umami for privacy-oriented site analytics. They process typical web request and usage signals, not your image content.',
    'With our current configuration, Umami and Cloudflare Web Analytics each retain analytics data for six months. Interface preferences such as theme, language, and default quality are stored in your browser’s localStorage.',
  ],
  trustHeading: 'Security and trust model',
  trustText:
    'PicShift is built around data minimization: your images are processed on your device, and we do not ask you to create an account to use the service. For full legal wording and updates, see the Privacy Policy page.',
};
const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'TechArticle',
  headline: title,
  description,
  url: canonical,
  inLanguage: lang,
  datePublished,
  dateModified,
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'PicShift' },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'PicShift', url: 'https://picshift.app' },
};
const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    {
      '@type': 'ListItem',
      position: 1,
      name: docsUi.home,
      item: htmlCanonicalUrl(`https://picshift.app/${lang}/`),
    },
    {
      '@type': 'ListItem',
      position: 2,
      name: docsUi.docs,
      item: docsHubUrl,
    },
    {
      '@type': 'ListItem',
      position: 3,
      name: title,
      item: canonical,
    },
  ],
};
const faqs = getDocsFaqs(lang, 'privacy-local-processing');
const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faqs.map((faq) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: faq.q,
    acceptedAnswer: {
      '@type': 'Answer',
      text: faq.a,
    },
  })),
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} lang={lang} pagePath={pagePath}>
  <Header lang={lang} pagePath={pagePath} />

  <main class="flex-1">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 sm:py-14">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-4 text-sm text-text-secondary">
        <a href={`/${lang}/`} class="hover:text-text-primary hover:underline">{docsUi.home}</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href={`/${lang}/docs`} class="hover:text-text-primary hover:underline">{docsUi.docs}</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-text-primary">{docsUi.privacyDocTitle}</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">
        {title}
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-text-secondary mb-8">
        {privacyDocContent.intro}
      </p>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{privacyDocContent.filesHeading}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          {privacyDocContent.filesItems.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{privacyDocContent.staysHeading}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          {privacyDocContent.staysItems.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{privacyDocContent.analyticsHeading}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          {privacyDocContent.analyticsItems.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{privacyDocContent.trustHeading}</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          {privacyDocContent.trustText}
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{verifyUi.docsVerifyHeading}</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary mb-3">{verifyUi.docsVerifyIntro}</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          {verifyUi.docsVerifySteps.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{verifyUi.docsBoundaryHeading}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          {verifyUi.docsBoundaryItems.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{verifyUi.docsEvidenceHeading}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          <li>
            {verifyUi.docsEvidenceItems[0]}
            {' '}
            <a href={localePath('/privacy', lang)} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.privacyPolicy}</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            {verifyUi.docsEvidenceItems[1]}
            {' '}
            <a href={localePath('/docs/format-compatibility', lang)} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.formatDocTitle}</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            {verifyUi.docsEvidenceItems[2]}
            {' '}
            <a href={localePath('/docs/image-quality-vs-file-size', lang)} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.qualityDocTitle}</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{docsUi.faq}</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {faqs.map((faq) => (
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card-bg p-4">
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-text-primary mb-1">{faq.q}</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">{faq.a}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{docsUi.relatedPages}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/docs/why-picshift`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.whyPicShiftDocTitle}</a></li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/privacy`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.privacyPolicy}</a></li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/docs`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.allDocs}</a></li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{docsUi.picShiftHome}</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">{docsUi.backToToolPages}</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-text-secondary">
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/heic-to-jpg`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{pageTranslations.tools['heic-to-jpg']?.h1 || 'HEIC to JPG Converter'}</a></li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/webp-to-jpg`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{pageTranslations.tools['webp-to-jpg']?.h1 || 'WebP to JPG Converter'}</a></li>
          <li><a href={`/${lang}/image-compressor`} class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">{pageTranslations.tools['image-compressor']?.h1 || 'Image Compressor'}</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary pt-4 border-t border-border">{docsUi.lastUpdated}: {dateModified}</p>
    </article>
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </main>

  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
